[src:on-base-percentage/1899-in-baseball] Buck Freeman of the Washington Senators leads all batters with 25 home runs during the regular season, more than double hit by Bobby Wallace of the St.
[src:on-base-percentage/1899-in-baseball] Louis Perfectos, who finished with 12 homers.
[src:on-base-percentage/1899-in-baseball] Freeman's tally was not surpassed until 1919, when Babe Ruth belted 29 home runs for the Boston Red Sox.
